Thank you to the Landmark Elders™️ for behaving this once so we could fully experience Mica Levi’s score without the usual disruptions. We did have to share the theatre with the world’s wettest cough but fine, I’ll take it.
Yanguary 2024 continues at the Siskel! Meet me at the Hard Rock Angela and teach me your ways.
Everybody gets to do an accent as a treat.

Never quite bought Adam Driver in the title role and the less said about Shailene the better (at one point there’s a reference to a French book she read and I thought “oh is this character supposed to be French? Is that what’s going on here?”). But Penelope Cruz is so good in what could have been just a paint by numbers role! I barely cared about the race but still could have watched three more hours of this. Beep beep, let’s ride!
First film of the year - Yanguary 2024 off to a great start!
Last film of 2023! Even though I wasn’t in an AMC (Siskel!), I loved ending the year with a heartbreak feels good in a place like this cry.

Penultimate movie of the year. At times it can feel a bit like we’re just waiting to hit the next historical checkpoint, but the performances keep the emotional stakes in the foreground. Theatre kids, amirite?
“It’s always wrestlemania, it’s never wrestle-depression.” - joke from Vill.
Perfect 3.5 star 90s movie that came out in 2023. Jamie Foxx is so good! They don’t make em like this anymore except in this case they did!

Movie: Home Alone 2: Lost in New York

Review: My sister had already watched Indiana Jones and the Dial of Destiny on the plane ride home for Christmas so we watched this as an family instead. Fittingly it is the ideal plane movie. Looks like it was made for $1 but was fun enough. Love Hugh Grant in his pervy era.
